            <div type="translation" resp="part:emfr">
                <p n="1">Prosperity! Fortune!</p>
                <p n="1">7th year of Vīra Cōḻa Irukkuvēl alias Kesarivarman.</p>
                <p n="1-2">
                    Whereas <gap reason="lost"/> Vēḷār made a petition stating that a <foreign>devadāna</foreign> should graciously be given for the expenses <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>aḻivu</foreign></supplied>
                    ...
                    <unclear>there is</unclear>
                    a <foreign>devadāna</foreign>.
                </p>
                <p n="2-4">
                    The boundaries for the the pond
                    ... are as follows:
                    <list>
                        <item>
                            the eastern boundary is east of the western boundary ... north of ... east of ...
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            the <supplied reason="lost">northern</supplied> boundary is south of ...
                        </item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p n="4">The land comprised within these four boundaries <supplied reason="lost">is</supplied> <gap reason="lost"/>.<note>The lacuna most probably consists in the measurements of the plot.</note></p>
                
                <p n="4">In this manner ... the signature of Cōḻamūvēntavēḷāṉ.</p>
                
                <p n="4"><supplied reason="subaudible">This is under the</supplied> protection of the Paṉmāheśvarars.</p>
                
                
